description:
Numerous elements combine to form Edinburgh Castle's distinct aroma:

1) Vinegar, from the fish & chips brought over from the Old Chelsea around the corner;

2) Piss, from the semi-functional toilets in the restrooms;

3) Feet, presumably from the gruff bartender;

4) Tears of shame; and,

5) Shit that other reviewers here are full of, since it is my team that beats all others at the Castle Quiz.

The quiz is the most entertaining that I've been to and seems to have the most creative and vulgar team names.

Also, they have a better than average selection of beer and a nice waitress.
